Converting to data type 'char' converts variables into cell arrays of character vectors rather than a character array. Storing text data as character arrays in a table is not recommended. When working with text data in a table or a timetable, consider using a string array or a categorical array.
Converted variables must maintain the same number of rows as the original variables.
